<subSubSection id="BB02F1DE1CEEBFB0F6D0E790428C62F8" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" type="description">
<paragraph id="044EDD09619EC080E13DA0110A584A64" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="86EFA0B3487629B99BB7F233EFFB3C45" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D31F662B06A455BA111D07FFA06118FF" authorityName="Boiss. &amp; Kotschy, Diagn. Pl. Orient. 7: 27. 1846. (Boissier" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus acanthocladus" order="Solanales" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acanthocladus">
<emphasis id="08F3A9608B9CAED53FF58295A2D2C256" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Convolvulus acanthocladus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Stems erect, straight and spreading at a very acute angle to the main axis, grey-sericeous and pilose with spreading hairs, branches spine-tipped but lateral spines lacking. Leaves linear, 5-15 
<normalizedToken id="6458411837C6B5A16EF51649B5587C7A" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm. Flowers solitary or paired in the uppermost leaf axils, sessile, characteristically overtopped by the spinescent branches; sepals 12-13 mm long, similar in shape to those of 
<taxonomicName id="85F192A5457D3D731EF7171FCA335980" authorityName="Boiss. &amp; Kotschy, Diagn. Pl. Orient. 7: 27. 1846. (Boissier" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus acanthocladus" order="Solanales" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acanthocladus">
<emphasis id="21C06BB5564F90F883D0754CCB946C5B" italics="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Convolvulus acanthocladus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but more abruptly caudate with a pronounced apical mucro and distinctly longer; corolla c. 2.5 cm long, white but pinkish in bud. [
<bibRefCitation id="309A0CC15DF06207E5D5AE6833C57A74" author="Rechinger, KH" journalOrPublisher="Anzeiger Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftlichen Klasse Osterreichische Akadamie der Wissenschaften" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="21 - 28" refId="B297" refString="Rechinger, KH, 1961. Notizen zur Orient-Flora, 5-10. Anzeiger Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftlichen Klasse Osterreichische Akadamie der Wissenschaften 98: 21 - 28" title="Notizen zur Orient-Flora, 5 - 10." volume="98" year="1961">Rechinger 1961</bibRefCitation>
: 22; 
<bibRefCitation id="9049BBCF0DCEAA5283D069AE514C3717" author="Rechinger, KH" editor="Rechinger, KH" journalOrPublisher="Akademische Druck und Verlagsanstalt, Graz" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 24" refId="B298" refString="Rechinger, KH, 1963. Convolvulaceae. In: Rechinger, KH, Ed., Flora Iranica. Akademische Druck und Verlagsanstalt, Graz: 1 - 24" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Iranica." year="1963">1963</bibRefCitation>
: 25; 
<bibRefCitation id="1AE809F0D8F9859B947B80DFBD0E1E21" author="Nowroozi, M" journalOrPublisher="Ministry of Jihad-e-Agriculture, Iran" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 110" refId="B244" refString="Nowroozi, M, 2002. Flora of Iran 40: Convolvulaceae. Ministry of Jihad-e-Agriculture, Iran: 1 - 110" title="Flora of Iran 40: Convolvulaceae" year="2002">Nowroozi 2002</bibRefCitation>
: 25 (plate), 100 (map)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
